               <persName type="alt">Eleutherus</persName>
               <persName type="alt">Eleftherios</persName>
               <persName type="alt">Liberalis</persName>
               <persName type="alt">Liberator</persName>
               <residence>Rome</residence>
               <floruit>Supposedly a bishop in Illyria, Dalmatia, with his mother, Anthia. He was a Roman, educated by Bishop Dynamius. At the age of twenty, Eleutherius himself became a bishop and was arrested for converting an imperial official. 
                  He was clubbed to death and Anthia was beheaded.</floruit>
               <death notAfter="0138">He was martyred during Emperor Hadrian.</death>
               <note type="commemoration"><date type="diesNatalis" ref="ethiocal:Hedar18">18 Ḫǝdār</date></note>
            </person>
            
         </listPerson>
